---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import LessonShell from "../../components/LessonShell.astro";
import ChatSim from "../../components/ChatSim.astro";
import Screencast from "../../components/Screencast.astro";
import { LESSONS } from "../../data/curriculum";

const lesson = LESSONS.find((l) => l.id === "chat-first")!;
---

<Layout title={`${lesson.title} · Learn AI`} description={lesson.blurb} currentId="chat-first">
    <LessonShell lesson={lesson}>
      <p>
        <strong>Chat assistants</strong> all share this shape: a centred conversation, a sidebar of past chats,
        and (sometimes) a panel on the right when the assistant produces something self-contained.
        The imitation below behaves like <a href="https://chat.openai.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">chat.openai.com</a>,
        <a href="https://claude.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener">claude.ai</a>, or
        <a href="https://gemini.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gemini.google.com</a>.
      </p>

      <Screencast slot="chat-loop" />

      <ChatSim prompts={["Hi", "Write a thank-you note", "Plan a 3-day Tokyo trip", "Build me a simple webpage"]} />

      <h2>What real chat apps add</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>An account so chats persist across devices.</li>
        <li><strong>File upload</strong> — PDFs, images, spreadsheets, audio.</li>
        <li><strong>Model picker</strong> — fast vs smart vs cheap (each vendor has a tier).</li>
        <li><strong>Projects / GPTs / Gems</strong> — covered next lesson.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="callout">
        <strong>Which chat app to pick?</strong> They're more alike than different for most tasks. Pick by:
        which model brand you want to support; what files you need to upload; what your team already uses;
        which one feels best to you. Switch any time — your prompts move with you.
      </div>

      <h2>First-run setting that's easy to miss</h2>
      <p>
        Every chat app has a "help improve our model" / "use my conversations for training" toggle.
        It's usually <em>on</em> by default. Decide it intentionally before you paste anything sensitive.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Claude.ai:</strong> Settings → Privacy → <em>Help improve Claude</em></li>
        <li><strong>ChatGPT:</strong> Settings → Data Controls → <em>Improve the model for everyone</em></li>
        <li><strong>Gemini:</strong> Activity → <em>Gemini Apps Activity</em></li>
      </ul>
      <p style="color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: 0.92rem;">
        Off = your chats aren't used to train future models. The trade-off: some features
        (memory, personalization) may be limited.
      </p>
    </LessonShell>
</Layout>
